Commentary: OUT! BOWLED'EM! OUTFOXED! Absolute jaffa from Leach and he provides an early breakthrough for England! Leach bustles from around the pegs, tosses it up, and lands it on the middle stump line. Abdullah Shafique draws his front foot out with a huge stride to defend it. But the ball lands, grips sharply, and turns prodigiously off the deck, leaving the batter. Shafique plays inside the line of the ball as it zips past the outside edge to clatter into the off stump. Commentary: OUT! TAKEN! The short mid-wicket fielder was tactically stationed there and Zak Crawley takes a stunning catch to dismiss the Pakistani skipper. Leach has his second wicket. Jack Leach stays over the stumps, drops it flat and fuller, just around off, Shan Masood strides ahead and tries to work it with the spin to the leg side. Commentary: A mix-up and that could have ended badly for Ayub! Tossed up, full and on off, Ayub lunges and taps it with soft hands to the right of cover-point. He sets off for the run but Kamran Ghulam is not interested and sends him back. The fielder is quick to get to the ball and releases a good quick throw to the keeper at the batting end. Ayub turns around and has to put the dive in to make the ground. The keeper, Jamie Smith whips the bails off quickly. It is referred upstairs. The replays show that Ayub's bat did pop up after the shoulder of the bat bounced off the turf but had some part of his glove ground inside the crease when the bails were taken off.

Commentary: OUT! CAUGHT! The plan to keep short mid off has worked finally for England. And a key wicket for the tourists, right before the Tea break. The 149-run stand is broken and Potts gets his first wicket. Matthew Potts charges in from over the stumps to the left-hander and lands it full, slightly nipping away off the pitch. Commentary: OUT! BOWLED! Shoaib Bashir breaks through for England! End of a fine knock by the debutant, Kamran Ghulam! Bashir drifts it in, on a nagging length, on middle and leg, Kamran skips down the track and shapes up to go back over the bowler's head with a straight bat. The ball does not turn and just goes on straight. He plays down the wrong line and gets beaten on the outside edge. The ball clips the leg stump and it is enough to dislodge the right bail. Bashir roars in delight. Ghulam is crossed with himself. He departs for 118 (224) with 5.4 overs left in the day.
Default_Commentary: 84.2: Shoaib Bashir to Kamran Ghulam, OUT! b Shoaib Bashir.
Howout: b Shoaib Bashir

Commentary: A huge appeal for LBW, but the umpire turns it down! After a long chat, Ben Stokes decides to send it upstairs. Looks very close though! Matthew Potts comes from wider on the crease and angles it into the batter, on middle and off, with a hint of inward movement, on a length. Mohammad Rizwan looks to play at it with a straight bat but misses on the inside edge and gets hit on the back pad. The Ultra Edge shows no spike and the Ball Tracking shows the impact and pitch to be right but the extra bounce to be taking the ball over leg stump. The onfield call stays and England lose another review.

Commentary: OUT! DRAGGED ON! This is the second from Sajid Khan and he is loving it! Why shouldn't he? He gets the big fish here. Sajid bowls it fuller and quicker, just outside off. Joe Root gets low on his knee to sweep it across the line towards his leg side but only gets the connection on the inner edge. The ball gets nicked, deflects from Root's boots, and rattles into the base of the off pole. Sajid Khan sprints and leaps to punch the air out of joy. Root stands there in disbelief as he knows that shot was not on this ball. He goes back for 34 off 54, and England lose their third!

Commentary: OUT! TAKEN! A huge appeal for caught behind down the leg side but turned down. Ben Stokes asks his fellow players and takes it upstairs. The slow motion shows it is off the thigh pad. Full and around off, lands and spins down leg sharply. Shafique goes on his back foot to flick but seems to miss. UltraEdge loading up...A little bit of murmur as the ball shaves past the inside edge. The third umpire says he can see a spike as it rolls past the inside edge and requests the on-field umpire to change his decision. Shafique has to go. Excellent grab from Jamie Smith down the leg side as it spun in sharply. England have the breakthrough.
